<br>
Seems to me if he's refuting crazy people who talk to aliens by channeling, then he's making some sense.<br>
<br>
Without doing the calculations, it seems highly likely that he's right, i.e. that a star would be quite a bit brighter than anything we see in the skies minus the sun and the moon, and we don't see ANYTHING at all, nothing, that is at that distance.<br>
<br>
None of this even considers the massive effects a brown dwarf would have on the orbit of the earth.  Planets in binary systems don't follow elliptical orbits, and it's pretty well established that the planets follow elliptical orbits.  The perturbations you'd expect in the orbit of the Earth would be massive.<br>
<br>
There just isn't room for a brown dwarf out there.<br>
